{{Other uses}} {{Redirect|Love bite|the British film|Love Bite}} {{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = Hickey | image = Love bite.jpg | alt = | caption = Hickeys on the neck. | pronounce = | field = | synonym = Kiss mark, love bite, bug bite | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }}
A '''hickey''', '''hickie''' or '''love bite''' in [[British English]], is a [[bruise]] or bruise-like mark caused by the [[kissing]] or sucking of the [[skin]], usually on the [[neck]] or [[arm]]. While biting might be part of giving a hickey, sucking is sufficient to burst small superficial [[blood vessels]] under the skin.
The origin of the word is from its earlier meaning of "pimple, skin lesion" (c. 1915); perhaps a sense extension and spelling variation from the earlier word meaning "small gadget, device; any unspecified object" which has an unknown origin (1909).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etymonline.com/word/hickie|title=hickie - Origin and meaning of hickie by Online Etymology Dictionary|website=www.etymonline.com}}</ref>
Hickeys typically last from 5 to 12 days and may be treated in the same way as other bruises.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ownarticles.com/how-long-do-hickeys-last |title=How Long Do Hickeys Last |date=April 15, 2016|website=ownarticles.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520071039/http://ownarticles.com/how-long-do-hickeys-last |archivedate=2016-05-20 |df= }}</ref> Ways to reduce the appearance of hickeys include icing recent hickeys to reduce swelling, rubbing them with a chilled spoon to remove the bruise, and applying a [[warm compress]] to older hickeys to dilate vessels and promote blood flow.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life/relationships/man-woman/Ouch-Thats-a-lovebite/articleshow/4680691.cms|title=Ouch! That's a lovebite! |accessdate=2010-01-18 |author=Amar, Charu |date=2009-11-06 |work=Man-Woman Relationships |publisher=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> They can be covered with a concealer or powder corresponding to the sufferer's skin tone, or a fake tan. Alternatively, articles of clothing such as [[scarf|scarves]], [[snood (headgear)|snoods]], [[polo neck|turtle necks]], or [[sleeve]]s may be used to conceal hickeys.
